file_content.text: Testing... testing... one, two, three. Commander?
This thing on? Commander?
Commander. You there?
Come in.
Oh, good. Shields are out of commission. Was actually easier than I thought it would be.
Shields are offline. Nabbed some parts. Should make a small fortune.
Shields are down. Ran into a few guards. Nothing I couldn't handle.
Gun controls are smashed. Ship is officially declawed.
I took out the guns. They could afford to up the security in this place.
Perfect timing! Guns are also down.
Good work. Distract Arcann's troops. And try not to steal everything.
Keep the Skytroopers busy.
Fine. Be boring.
It's for the Alliance...
Your work is done. Wait for us at the shuttle.
Head back where it's safe.
No time to rest. Kill everyone you come across.
Good. Now leave no survivors.
Easy enough. I've been itching for a fight.
And take their stuff, right? Right.
Already headed that way.
I came here to fight. I'll be at the shuttle before takeoff. Until then, I'm dropping bodies.
